FT  10 JUL 92 / Technology (Worth Watching): The potato makes a new kind of
chip
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
An unusual use has been found for the humble potato. Using natural vegetable
starch found in potatoes, the London-based AI Packagings group has launched
what is believed to be the first 100 per cent biodegradable and water
soluble, free flow, light-weight cushioning material.
'Renature' which is flexible, hollow and looks like expanded polystyrene
chips, provides all-round packaging protection for goods in transit. The new
material has a high resistance to moisture, yet dissolves quickly when in
direct contact with water.
