FT  09 JUL 92 / International Company News: Bank of Boston to open in Mexico
City
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
NEW ENGLAND-based Bank of Boston has received approval from the Mexican
government to open an office in Mexico City, Reuter reports.
About half of the bank's international operations are in Latin America. The
bank has over 100 offices in 25 countries and international operations
account for 18 per cent of the company's total assets.
