FT  09 JUL 92 / Observer: Smokelore
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
An Indian takes a trip from his reservation to a Las Vegas casino. But his
luck is out, and he loses every cent. There being no telephones on the
reservation, he puts out a smoke signal: 'Send money, send money, send money
. . .'. Alas, it happens to be a day when the Atomic Energy Authority is
testing at nearby Yucca Flats, and his message is almost obliterated by a
great mushroom cloud.
Even so, he is soon rewarded with word from home. 'Sending money, sending
money, sending money . . .' comes the signal back.
'And there's no need to shout.'
