ALTHOUGH there is no auction guidance from the main primary markets in
Australia, New Zealand and South Africa prices are still subject to the
vagaries of volatile currency markets. Weakness in the US dollar has
recently been slightly outpaced by weakness in the Australian dollar, and
related prices in Europe have been plumbing their recent lows. Inevitably
this downward drift does not help those who are trying to persuade buyers to
move in. The uncertainty and lack of confidence keeps business quiet, which
in turn tends to soften selling prices further.
