FT  09 JUL 92 / UK Company News: Elswick expects to pay interim dividend
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Elswick, the print and packaging concern, said that following the disposal
of its lossmaking cycles division, it had been successful in its court
application for consent to utilise the share premium account in order to
eliminate the deficit on its profit and loss account.
Mr Harold Cross, chairman, therefore reaffirmed his statement with the last
annual report that an interim dividend for the current year would be paid in
January 1993.
The last final dividend was omitted leaving a total of 0.22p (0.6p) for the
12 months to January 31 1992. Pre-tax profits for that year were static at
Pounds 2.25m (Pounds 2.22m).
