FT  08 JUL 92 / International Company News: Anti-histamine warning
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL ABRAHAMS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE US Food and Drug Administration yesterday asked Marion Merrell Dow, the
American pharmaceuticals group, to warn doctors that Seldane, its
anti-histamine, is potentially dangerous to certain patients.
The drug had worldwide sales of Dollars 768m last year, of which Dollars
534m were in the US. In the UK, the company claims Seldane is the
best-selling over-the-counter remedy.
The FDA said the drug was potentially dangerous when used by patients with
damaged liver or those taking two other drugs, Ketoconazole, an anti-fungal
treatment, and Erythromycin, an antibiotic. Although one patient has died,
the FDA stressed reactions were rare.
Marion Merrell Dow said it was changing the labels, warning of such problems
and the need to restrict dosing to less than 120mg a day.
