<HEADLINE>
FT  08 JUL 92 / Observer: Employment tip
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Did you know that Bengt Dennis, governor of the Swedish Riksbank - the
oldest central bank in the world - is one of the most lowly paid members of
his fraternity?
He earns a mere 55,000 crowns a month (Pounds 5,230) from his employment in
Stockholm. But he manages to double his annual earnings as a result of
plentiful emoluments from the Bank for International Settlements, of which
he is currently president - a mandate which runs out at the end of next
year.
</TEXT>
